strings.Value: "By the gods, what are you?!"
[Attack] "Die, vile creature!"
"So you were the one the goblins were after?"
"Where have you come from to our world?"
"I have helped you. Where is my reward?"
[Leave] "The path is clear. I hope you find a way back. Farewell!"
"What is your name?"
"I found a corpse in the bushes! Was it you who killed that traveler?"
"You're limping... are you hurt?"
"Help. Path. Home. Joy. Friend."
"Traveler. Passer-by. Lost. Wandering."
"Predators. Murder. Fear. Hide-and-seek."
{n}The creature in front of you is silent for a few moments, then speaks.{/n} "Multitude. Fey. Primeval."
{n}The strange creature in front of you points at the bushes it emerged from.{/n} "Bag. Items. Multitude."
"Gratitude. Farewell."
{n}The creature emits a series of sharp clicks that vary in pitch. Most likely, this is its name, but you would be hard-pressed to repeat it.{/n}
"Past. Innocence. Fear."
"Agreement. Pain. Enemy. Run. Loss."

{n}Jubilost's eyes widen. He pulls a notepad from his pocket and flips through it frantically, looking between it and the creature.{/n} "Wait, where was it...? Aha! Right! I can't believe it. Do you know what this is? Goblins take me, this is a phase spider, straight from the {g|First World}First World{/g}! I have so many questions... Why, why did I never learn to speak Aklo when I had the chance?!"
"Incredible! You get to see so many wonders in these lands!"
